Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c, indicating impaired glucose control or possible diabetes, and low HDL cholesterol, which increases cardiovascular risk. Total CO₂ is slightly low, which may suggest mild metabolic acidosis or compensation. Other parameters, including renal function, electrolytes, and lipid profile, are within normal limits. Clinical correlation and follow-up are recommended.
